ere they auto-redeemed at resolution?\n\n**Hypothesis:** PM 5-min markets likely auto-redeem via the NegRiskAdapter. The CLOB balance discrepancy ($871 vs ~$930 expected) is likely just a CLOB API timing issue, not $2K+ in locked tokens.\n\n**Evidence for auto-redemption:**\n- Apr 3 balance drops were $1.84-$10.56 per cycle, NOT the full $11.76 bet size\n- This suggests partial redemption of winning shares is happening between cycles\n- The 5-min gap between bet and resolution is short enough for auto-redemption\n\n**Decision:** Stop chasing the balance mystery. Real P&L from outcomes = +$211. CLOB balance = noisy but directionally correct. Focus on trading strategy, not accounting.\n\n**Next:** P2 smart entry\n\n---\n## 2026-04-03 22:09 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] MEMORY.md Updated: Corrected P&L + Bug #4 Documented\n\n**Task:** P4 alpha \u2014 update MEMORY.md with corrected P&L narrative and Bug #4\n\n**Updates to MEMORY.md:**\n1. Added \"Real P&L\" section: +$211 all-time from trade outcomes (not CLOB balance)\n2. Documented Bug #4 (daily loss limit never resets) in Critical Bugs section\n3. Updated timestamp\n\n**Apr 3 Day ",
